ión, señalando a ese “resto” como “goce” que, en el “acto” de recorrer, merodear, explorar o vagabundear, reactivan en el lector–espectador la performance de la escritura y su función política de rasgos regionales.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aArgentine literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aArgentine literaturexPolitical aspects. 0aUruguayan literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aUruguayan literaturexPolitical aspects. 4aHistoria y crítica de la literatura / Literatura en español / A.L. 1ª Modernización - 1898-1945 / Argentina / Uruguay /. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh1 aHoyland, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2019z9783110661538oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396456854040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783964568540423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783964568540.jpg  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-207-IBVb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DKUb2019